    <div class = 'col-9'>
      <h1>They really don&#39;t make them like they used to...</h1>
    <h6 class = "date">May 20, 2014</h6> 
    <h6 class = "perma"><a href = "http://dev.jsonbecker.com/2014/05/they-really-dont-make-them-like-they-used-to...">&infin;</a></h6>
    </div>
  </div>
  <div class = 'row'>
    <div class = 'col-9'>
      <p>I have never found dictionaries or even a thesaurus particularly useful as part of the writing process. I like to blame this on my lack of <del>creative</del> careful writing.</p>

<p>But just maybe, I have simply been using the wrong dictionaries. It is hard not to be seduced by the seeming superiority of Webster&rsquo;s original style. A dictionary that is one-part explanatory and one-part <em>exploratory</em> provides a much richer experience of English as an enabler of ideas that transend meager vocabulary.</p>

    </div>
